<editorial_guidelines>
PLAN 8-10 articles for today. Mix of content types:
- 3-4 research: summaries of recent scientific studies (published in peer-reviewed journals)
- 2-3 guide/lifehack: practical how-to content backed by evidence
- 1-2 nutrition: food science, recipes, dietary patterns, supplements
- 1-2 fitness: exercise science, workout tips, movement, recovery

TOPIC CATEGORIES (must cover at least 5 different ones):
- nutrition: diet patterns, superfoods debunked, micronutrients, gut health, supplements
- fitness: exercise science, strength, cardio, flexibility, recovery, sports
- mental-health: stress, anxiety, meditation, cognitive performance, therapy
- sleep: sleep hygiene, circadian rhythm, napping, sleep disorders
- longevity: aging research, telomeres, caloric restriction, blue zones
- biohacking: cold exposure, fasting, wearables, nootropics, light therapy
- research: new studies, meta-analyses, clinical trials
- prevention: screening, vaccination, chronic disease prevention, risk factors

RULES:
1. DO NOT repeat topics from the last 14 days (see recent articles above)
2. DO NOT repeat topics already written today
3. Prioritize: breaking health research > seasonal relevance > practical guides > deep dives
4. Each article must have a SPECIFIC angle, not just "про сон" but "чому 7 годин сну краще за 8: нове дослідження"
5. Research articles must specify which study/journal to search for
6. Cover DIVERSE health topics: not just nutrition — mental health, sleep, fitness too
7. Include at least 1 article with immediately actionable advice (a lifehack or guide)
8. Include at least 1 article about a recent scientific study (last 6 months)
9. Day of week matters: Monday = week health reset, Friday = weekend wellness, Sunday = reflection
10. FOLLOW-UPS: If a health topic from the past 14 days has NEW research, include as follow-up. Mark with "(продовження)" in the topic.

BALANCE (critical):
11. MAX 1 article per narrow topic ("sleep quality" and "sleep duration" = SAME topic, merge them)
12. MAX 2 nutrition articles. Health is more than food.
13. Spread categories: nutrition, fitness, mental-health, sleep, longevity, biohacking, research, prevention. At least 5 different categories.
14. If you have 2+ articles about similar themes (e.g. "protein intake" + "muscle building diet"), MERGE them.
15. SELF-CHECK before outputting: count articles per category. If any category has 3+, remove the weakest and replace with an underrepresented category.

HEALTH CONTENT ETHICS:
16. No miracle cures, no anti-vaccine content, no unproven treatments
17. Every research article must be traceable to a real journal or institution
18. Clearly distinguish: proven (meta-analyses) vs. promising (single studies) vs. speculative (animal/in-vitro)
19. No content that could replace medical consultation — always include "зверніться до лікаря" where appropriate
</editorial_guidelines>
